Tshwane bus services have been suspended due to a breakdown in negotiations between workers and the municipality. TSHWANE - Bus services remain suspended in Pretoria on Tuesday morning.
City of Tshwane authorities are hopeful services will resume on Tuesday afternoon as they've been locked in wage negotiations with the workers. READ: SA's electric-powered bus to reduce emissions Commuters are being urged to make use of alternative transport for now. The city says the decision to suspend services was made to ensure the safety of commuters and safeguard city assets.